_:N94bc361f9f9a448c976aeb497b69fdbe <http://schema.org/name> "Michael Vance" .
_:N94bc361f9f9a448c976aeb497b69fdbe <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Michael Vance joined the Civil Nuclear Constabulary (<abbr title=\"Civil Nuclear Constabulary\">CNC</abbr>) in 2004, having previously served in the Royal Irish Regiment in the armed forces.</p>\n\n<p>He has been a police officer since 1997, initially serving with the Royal Ulster Constabulary and Police Service of Northern Ireland Full Time Reserve.</p>\n\n<p>During his career with the <abbr title=\"Civil Nuclear Constabulary\">CNC</abbr> he has worked at all ranks up to Assistant Chief Constable including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Tactical Response Group</li>\n  <li>Operational Firearms Commander</li>\n  <li>Tactical Firearms Commander</li>\n  <li>Post Incident Manager</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>As an experienced <abbr title=\"Civil Nuclear Constabulary\">CNC</abbr> senior leader, he has been the Divisional Commander for each <abbr title=\"Civil Nuclear Constabulary\">CNC</abbr> Operational Division, developing local response arrangements in support of site licensed companies in a highly regulated environment.</p>\n\n<p>As an accredited Strategic Firearms Commander, he has been responsible for armed protection of all designated nuclear and non-nuclear sites across the UK. In his current role he is also responsible for domestic and international armed escorts of nuclear material. He took up the role of T/<abbr title=\"Assistant Chief Constable\">ACC</abbr> - Operations in 2023 and was substantively promoted in 2024.  </p>\n\n" .
_:Nae094b9339c94c31a881763a467049f0 <http://schema.org/itemListElement> _:Nbb2fd402eeea41ae996622a8890c06bf .
